Job_Description:
The Twin Lakes YMCA is hiring Youth Sports Officials. This is a part-time position.
Must possess some knowledge of rules and policies in various sports such as basketball, volleyball, soccer, football and baseball.
Must be available to work Saturdays from 8:00am to 6:00pm, as well as some week days from 4:30pm to 9pm.
Experience as a sports referee preferred but not required.
Must be able to pass a pre-employment drug screen, criminal history background check, sex offender registry check and reference checks.
Free individual YMCA of Central Texas membership and discounts on family membership.
Send resume detailing your experience to callen@ymcactx.org or apply online at: http://ymcactx.org/careers
Job requirements include:
Must be able to work weeknights as well as Saturdays from 8am to 6pm;
Must possess some knowledge of rules and policies in various sports such as basketball, baseball, football, soccer and volleyball;
Have a general knowledge of fitness and wellness;
Have strong communication and organizational skills;
Have a neat appearance and be well-groomed;
Be CPR/AED and First Aid certified or willing to be certified within first 30 days of employment;
Be willing to uphold the YMCA’s core values of caring, honesty, responsibility respect, and faith
Be able to pass reference check, pre-employment drug screen, background check and sex offender check.

Overview
Able is a purpose-driven company focused on making the overall population fitter, healthier, and happier by providing a 360-degree personalized approach to weight care for tens of thousands of people worldwide.
We are customer-obsessed, authentic, and super pumped to create innovative tech solutions that are accessible and will impact and improve the lives of our customers.
Able
Able is different.
It provides a science-backed, comprehensive program personalized to users' biology and lifestyle and supported by 1-on-1 coaching. It's the safest and most effective way to improve metabolic health and achieve sustained weight care.
The team
You will be joining a strong team of >70 people with high talent density who enjoy working in our fast-paced, 100% remote environment. Our team is fully international and passionate about building the future of health and weight care for our customers.
About the role
A great coach can change a life!
Do you want to pioneer health for future generations but are tired of being bogged down with advertising and marketing yourself? Our coaching platform matches you with subscribers focused on sustaining their weight goals and improving their overall health, so you can spend more time coaching and less time marketing.
Able provides a science-backed, comprehensive program that is focused on personalization, biology and lifestyle and supported by 1-on-1 coaching to help users achieve lasting weight goals and optimal metabolic health.
By providing this coaching and a personalized program that takes into account nutrition, sleep, hydration, movement, emotions and medication as appropriate, Able helps clients reach their happy weight and maintain it while improving their overall health and confidence.
We’re looking for certified health coaches who are self-starters with a passion for helping people become the best versions of themselves - if this is you, then read on! We know that change is hard, and there is always something we can improve in our lifestyle. Able is about making positive changes to lifestyle no matter where you are in your journey. Small changes equal big rewards long term. We guide, support, encourage, and educate.
So let’s talk about you. You have the desire and motivation to inspire others at every step of their health and wellness journeys. You advocate for a holistic approach to health and lifestyle and are knowledgeable in the pillars of health including sleep, stress/stress management, foods/eating, hydration, consistent physical movement, and positive relationships. You strive to build rapport, are an excellent listener, and are empathetic to the challenges around habit change. Your primary goal will be to keep your subscribers engaged with you and use the app to help support them to reach their goals. We have a proprietary coaching and subscriber platform that allows for various different formats to suit our subscribers - face-to-face calls, voice calls, voice messaging, and text chat messaging.
Please note:
At Able, we believe in a continuous recruitment process. This means that we are always on the lookout for talented individuals to join our team of Health Coaches.
To apply for the role of Health Coach, simply submit your application and we will promptly review it. Successful applicants will be invited to complete a 1-way video interview.
As we onboard new clients, we will review the video interviews of our Health Coaches and extend job offers to those who meet our standards. Please be aware that the timeline for this process may vary based on our capacity to acquire new clients.
Our aim is to make the recruitment process as efficient and fair as possible. We welcome the opportunity to connect with you and hear about your passion for health and wellness.
What you’ll do
Establish rapport with an ongoing relationship to subscribers and offer support and guidance in developing personalized and measurable health goals and plans;
Work a flexible schedule based on your subscriber needs & schedules;
Utilize Able’s variable coaching formats to accommodate the unique physical, psychosocial, cultural, and age-specific needs of each subscriber;
Respond to subscriber health-related queries in an ethical and caring way;
Communicate clearly and with confidence in a one-on-one situation;
Assist subscribers in their health journey by facilitating lifestyle modifications around Able’s holistic pillars of health and not focusing on calorie counting;
Assist subscribers with their whole-food meal plans if dietary needs/wants to require healthier swaptions;
Guide subscribers through the main features of the app and encourage them to use it more;
Ensure you follow the coaching code of conduct, policies, and procedures and strive for retention;
Stay informed on the latest nutrition and health techniques and methods.
About you
Have related wellness experience and training (nutrition education, sports medicine, personal coaching, coaching diploma from a nationally recognized accredited program (i.e. National Board for Health and Wellness Coaching, UKHCA, etc.);
Empathetic and compassionate attitude towards subscribers who may be sensitive, vulnerable, or concerned about their weight and lifestyle;
Highly organized with excellent time management skills;
Confident, professional communicator with excellent written/verbal digital skills and a motivating attitude;
Reliable internet connection and Macbook (with minimum M1 chip) or iPad
Excellent command of the English language - Must be Proficient and at first language level;
You must currently be eligible to work and remain indefinitely without any restrictions in the country to which you are making an application. Proof will be required to support your application.
Ability to adapt to an ever-changing tech environment where new features occur frequently. We’re all about making everything better!
Nice to have
Having worked in the past in the health and fitness-related area is an advantage;
Telehealth experience;
Having worked in the past in cross-functional teams in a fast-paced, agile environment.
Our coaching values
We ask coaches to embody these values so they can make clients successful and continue coaching them long-term. Furthermore, these values instruct us in how to make decisions and prioritize our time and energy:

Connection is the basis of everything we do;
We are present and devoted to every client;
We look at the client as a whole;
Our program is flexible and sustainable;
We learn from every experience to take positive steps forward.
Life at Able
By joining Able, you’ll become part of a team that picks each other up, collaborates daily, and works hard, fast, and smart because they’re motivated and passionate about being the best in the industry. We thrive on innovation, we push the boundaries, and we’re proud of the work we do that really helps thousands of people live happier and healthier lives!
Equality
All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, race, color, religion, national origin, disability, protected Veteran status, age, or any other characteristic protected by law.
